quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,98,"On the Day of Resurrection he will lead his people and conduct them into the Fire: an evil goal for the incoming"
  11,99,"They are pursued by a curse in this [world], as well as on the Day of Resurrection; evil is the award conferred [upon them]"
  11,100,"These are from the accounts of the townships, which We recount to you. Of them, there are some that still stand, and some that have been mown down"
  11,101,"We did not wrong them, but they wronged themselves. When your Lord’s edict came, their gods whom they would invoke besides Allah were of no avail to them in any wise, and they did not increase them in anything but ruin"
  11,102,Such is the seizing of your Lord when He seizes the townships that are wrongdoing. Indeed His seizing is painful and severe
  11,103,"There is indeed a sign in that for those who fear the punishment of the Hereafter. That is a day on which all mankind will be gathered, and it is a day witnessed [by all creatures]"
  11,104,And We do not defer it but for a determinate term
  11,105,"The day it comes, no one shall speak except by His leave. [On that day,] some of them will be wretched and [some] felicitous"
  11,106,"As for the wretched, they shall be in the Fire: their lot therein will be groaning and wailing"
  11,107,They shall remain in it for as long as the heavens and the earth endure—except what your Lord may wish; indeed your Lord does whatever He desires
  11,108,"As for the felicitous, they will be in paradise. They will remain in it for as long as the heavens and the earth endure—except what your Lord may wish—an endless bounty"